From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 09:40:19 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 9.5 Session A: temporary diagnostic logging
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds [krt] log lines around the comment controller hot path:
- when the controller registers with ICommentService.
- when the registry fires onDidChange (each diff URI mount).
- when setCommentsForPr is called (PR loaded / cache hit).
- when applyForPr fans out (per-PR resource count).
- when getDocumentComments runs (per-URI threads / ranges count).
- when KrtMonacoDiffView registers a base/head URI pair.

These show up in the dev console (Help → Toggle Developer Tools)
prefixed with '[krt]'. Once Session A's behavior is verified the
logging will be rolled back (or pruned to the must-have lines).
---
 .../workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtMonacoDiff.ts |  3 +++
 .../contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPrCommentController.ts  | 11 ++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

